{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"You know, I've talked about some of these projects before --"},{"time":3000,"text":"about the human genome and what that might mean,"},{"time":7000,"text":"and discovering new sets of genes."},{"time":10000,"text":"We're actually starting at a new point:"},{"time":13000,"text":"we've been digitizing biology,"},{"time":17000,"text":"and now we're trying to go from that digital code"},{"time":20000,"text":"into a new phase of biology"},{"time":22000,"text":"with designing and synthesizing life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25000,"text":"So, we've always been trying to ask big questions."},{"time":30000,"text":"\"What is life?\" is something that I think many biologists"},{"time":32000,"text":"have been trying to understand"},{"time":34000,"text":"at various levels."},{"time":36000,"text":"We've tried various approaches,"},{"time":39000,"text":"paring it down to minimal components."},{"time":43000,"text":"We've been digitizing it now for almost 20 years;"},{"time":45000,"text":"when we sequenced the human genome,"},{"time":47000,"text":"it was going from the analog world of biology"},{"time":50000,"text":"into the digital world of the computer."},{"time":54000,"text":"Now we're trying to ask, \"Can we regenerate life"},{"time":58000,"text":"or can we create new life"},{"time":60000,"text":"out of this digital universe?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":63000,"text":"This is the map of a small organism,"},{"time":66000,"text":"Mycoplasma genitalium,"},{"time":68000,"text":"that has the smallest genome for a species"},{"time":71000,"text":"that can self-replicate in the laboratory,"},{"time":74000,"text":"and we've been trying to just see if"},{"time":76000,"text":"we can come up with an even smaller genome."},{"time":80000,"text":"We're able to knock out on the order of 100 genes"},{"time":82000,"text":"out of the 500 or so that are here."},{"time":85000,"text":"When we look at its metabolic map,"},{"time":87000,"text":"it's relatively simple"},{"time":89000,"text":"compared to ours --"},{"time":91000,"text":"trust me, this is simple --"},{"time":93000,"text":"but when we look at all the genes"},{"time":95000,"text":"that we can knock out one at a time,"},{"time":98000,"text":"it's very unlikely that this would yield"},{"time":100000,"text":"a living cell."},{"time":103000,"text":"So we decided the only way forward"},{"time":105000,"text":"was to actually synthesize this chromosome"},{"time":108000,"text":"so we could vary the components"},{"time":111000,"text":"to ask some of these most fundamental questions."},{"time":115000,"text":"And so we started down the road of:"},{"time":117000,"text":"can we synthesize a chromosome?"},{"time":121000,"text":"Can chemistry permit making"},{"time":123000,"text":"these really large molecules"},{"time":125000,"text":"where we've never been before?"},{"time":127000,"text":"And if we do, can we boot up a chromosome?"},{"time":130000,"text":"A chromosome, by the way, is just a piece of inert chemical material."},{"time":134000,"text":"So, our pace of digitizing life has been increasing"},{"time":137000,"text":"at an exponential pace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140000,"text":"Our ability to write the genetic code"},{"time":143000,"text":"has been moving pretty slowly"},{"time":145000,"text":"but has been increasing,"},{"time":148000,"text":"and our latest point would put it on, now, an exponential curve."},{"time":153000,"text":"We started this over 15 years ago."},{"time":155000,"text":"It took several stages, in fact,"},{"time":158000,"text":"starting with a bioethical review before we did the first experiments."},{"time":162000,"text":"But it turns out synthesizing DNA"},{"time":164000,"text":"is very difficult."},{"time":166000,"text":"There are tens of thousands of machines around the world"},{"time":169000,"text":"that make small pieces of DNA --"},{"time":171000,"text":"30 to 50 letters in length --"},{"time":174000,"text":"and it's a degenerate process, so the longer you make the piece,"},{"time":177000,"text":"the more errors there are."},{"time":179000,"text":"So we had to create a new method"},{"time":181000,"text":"for putting these little pieces together and correct all the errors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"And this was our first attempt, starting with the digital information"},{"time":188000,"text":"of the genome of phi X174."},{"time":190000,"text":"It's a small virus that kills bacteria."},{"time":194000,"text":"We designed the pieces, went through our error correction"},{"time":197000,"text":"and had a DNA molecule"},{"time":199000,"text":"of about 5,000 letters."},{"time":202000,"text":"The exciting phase came when we took this piece of inert chemical"},{"time":206000,"text":"and put it in the bacteria,"},{"time":208000,"text":"and the bacteria started to read this genetic code,"},{"time":212000,"text":"made the viral particles."},{"time":214000,"text":"The viral particles then were released from the cells"},{"time":216000,"text":"and came back and killed the E. coli."},{"time":219000,"text":"I was talking to the oil industry recently"},{"time":222000,"text":"and I said they clearly understood that model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":228000,"text":"They laughed more than you guys are. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":232000,"text":"And so, we think this is a situation"},{"time":234000,"text":"where the software can actually build its own hardware"},{"time":237000,"text":"in a biological system."},{"time":239000,"text":"But we wanted to go much larger:"},{"time":241000,"text":"we wanted to build the entire bacterial chromosome --"},{"time":244000,"text":"it's over 580,000 letters of genetic code --"},{"time":248000,"text":"so we thought we'd build them in cassettes the size of the viruses"},{"time":251000,"text":"so we could actually vary the cassettes"},{"time":253000,"text":"to understand"},{"time":255000,"text":"what the actual components of a living cell are."},{"time":258000,"text":"Design is critical,"},{"time":260000,"text":"and if you're starting with digital information in the computer,"},{"time":263000,"text":"that digital information has to be really accurate."},{"time":267000,"text":"When we first sequenced this genome in 1995,"},{"time":270000,"text":"the standard of accuracy was one error per 10,000 base pairs."},{"time":274000,"text":"We actually found, on resequencing it,"},{"time":276000,"text":"30 errors; had we used that original sequence,"},{"time":279000,"text":"it never would have been able to be booted up."},{"time":282000,"text":"Part of the design is designing pieces"},{"time":284000,"text":"that are 50 letters long"},{"time":287000,"text":"that have to overlap with all the other 50-letter pieces"},{"time":290000,"text":"to build smaller subunits"},{"time":292000,"text":"we have to design so they can go together."},{"time":295000,"text":"We design unique elements into this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298000,"text":"You may have read that we put watermarks in."},{"time":300000,"text":"Think of this:"},{"time":302000,"text":"we have a four-letter genetic code -- A, C, G and T."},{"time":305000,"text":"Triplets of those letters"},{"time":308000,"text":"code for roughly 20 amino acids,"},{"time":310000,"text":"such that there's a single letter designation"},{"time":313000,"text":"for each of the amino acids."},{"time":315000,"text":"So we can use the genetic code to write out words,"},{"time":318000,"text":"sentences, thoughts."},{"time":321000,"text":"Initially, all we did was autograph it."},{"time":323000,"text":"Some people were disappointed there was not poetry."},{"time":326000,"text":"We designed these pieces so"},{"time":328000,"text":"we can just chew back with enzymes;"},{"time":332000,"text":"there are enzymes that repair them and put them together."},{"time":335000,"text":"And we started making pieces,"},{"time":337000,"text":"starting with pieces that were 5,000 to 7,000 letters,"},{"time":341000,"text":"put those together to make 24,000-letter pieces,"},{"time":345000,"text":"then put sets of those going up to 72,000."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"At each stage, we grew up these pieces in abundance"},{"time":351000,"text":"so we could sequence them"},{"time":353000,"text":"because we're trying to create a process that's extremely robust"},{"time":356000,"text":"that you can see in a minute."},{"time":359000,"text":"We're trying to get to the point of automation."},{"time":362000,"text":"So, this looks like a basketball playoff."},{"time":364000,"text":"When we get into these really large pieces"},{"time":366000,"text":"over 100,000 base pairs,"},{"time":370000,"text":"they won't any longer grow readily in E. coli --"},{"time":372000,"text":"it exhausts all the modern tools of molecular biology --"},{"time":376000,"text":"and so we turned to other mechanisms."},{"time":380000,"text":"We knew there's a mechanism called homologous recombination"},{"time":383000,"text":"that biology uses to repair DNA"},{"time":386000,"text":"that can put pieces together."},{"time":389000,"text":"Here's an example of it:"},{"time":390000,"text":"there's an organism called"},{"time":391000,"text":"Deinococcus radiodurans"},{"time":393000,"text":"that can take three millions rads of radiation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396000,"text":"You can see in the top panel, its chromosome just gets blown apart."},{"time":400000,"text":"Twelve to 24 hours later, it put it"},{"time":403000,"text":"back together exactly as it was before."},{"time":405000,"text":"We have thousands of organisms that can do this."},{"time":408000,"text":"These organisms can be totally desiccated;"},{"time":410000,"text":"they can live in a vacuum."},{"time":413000,"text":"I am absolutely certain that life can exist in outer space,"},{"time":416000,"text":"move around, find a new aqueous environment."},{"time":419000,"text":"In fact, NASA has shown a lot of this is out there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423000,"text":"Here's an actual micrograph of the molecule we built"},{"time":427000,"text":"using these processes, actually just using yeast mechanisms"},{"time":431000,"text":"with the right design of the pieces we put them in;"},{"time":434000,"text":"yeast puts them together automatically."},{"time":437000,"text":"This is not an electron micrograph;"},{"time":439000,"text":"this is just a regular photomicrograph."},{"time":441000,"text":"It's such a large molecule"},{"time":443000,"text":"we can see it with a light microscope."},{"time":446000,"text":"These are pictures over about a six-second period."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"So, this is the publication we had just a short while ago."},{"time":453000,"text":"This is over 580,000 letters of genetic code;"},{"time":456000,"text":"it's the largest molecule ever made by humans of a defined structure."},{"time":461000,"text":"It's over 300 million molecular weight."},{"time":464000,"text":"If we printed it out at a 10 font with no spacing,"},{"time":467000,"text":"it takes 142 pages"},{"time":469000,"text":"just to print this genetic code."},{"time":473000,"text":"Well, how do we boot up a chromosome? How do we activate this?"},{"time":476000,"text":"Obviously, with a virus it's pretty simple;"},{"time":479000,"text":"it's much more complicated dealing with bacteria."},{"time":482000,"text":"It's also simpler when you go"},{"time":484000,"text":"into eukaryotes like ourselves:"},{"time":486000,"text":"you can just pop out the nucleus"},{"time":488000,"text":"and pop in another one,"},{"time":490000,"text":"and that's what you've all heard about with cloning."},{"time":493000,"text":"With bacteria and Archaea, the chromosome is integrated into the cell,"},{"time":497000,"text":"but we recently showed that we can do a complete transplant"},{"time":501000,"text":"of a chromosome from one cell to another"},{"time":503000,"text":"and activate it."},{"time":506000,"text":"We purified a chromosome from one microbial species --"},{"time":510000,"text":"roughly, these two are as distant as human and mice --"},{"time":513000,"text":"we added a few extra genes"},{"time":515000,"text":"so we could select for this chromosome,"},{"time":517000,"text":"we digested it with enzymes"},{"time":519000,"text":"to kill all the proteins,"},{"time":521000,"text":"and it was pretty stunning when we put this in the cell --"},{"time":524000,"text":"and you'll appreciate"},{"time":526000,"text":"our very sophisticated graphics here."},{"time":529000,"text":"The new chromosome went into the cell."},{"time":532000,"text":"In fact, we thought this might be as far as it went,"},{"time":534000,"text":"but we tried to design the process a little bit further."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537000,"text":"This is a major mechanism of evolution right here."},{"time":540000,"text":"We find all kinds of species"},{"time":542000,"text":"that have taken up a second chromosome"},{"time":544000,"text":"or a third one from somewhere,"},{"time":546000,"text":"adding thousands of new traits"},{"time":548000,"text":"in a second to that species."},{"time":550000,"text":"So, people who think of evolution"},{"time":552000,"text":"as just one gene changing at a time"},{"time":554000,"text":"have missed much of biology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557000,"text":"There are enzymes called restriction enzymes"},{"time":559000,"text":"that actually digest DNA."},{"time":561000,"text":"The chromosome that was in the cell"},{"time":563000,"text":"doesn't have one;"},{"time":565000,"text":"the chromosome we put in does."},{"time":567000,"text":"It got expressed and it recognized"},{"time":569000,"text":"the other chromosome as foreign material,"},{"time":572000,"text":"chewed it up, and so we ended up"},{"time":574000,"text":"just with a cell with the new chromosome."},{"time":578000,"text":"It turned blue because of the genes we put in it."},{"time":581000,"text":"And with a very short period of time,"},{"time":583000,"text":"all the characteristics of one species were lost"},{"time":586000,"text":"and it converted totally into the new species"},{"time":589000,"text":"based on the new software that we put in the cell."},{"time":592000,"text":"All the proteins changed,"},{"time":594000,"text":"the membranes changed;"},{"time":596000,"text":"when we read the genetic code, it's exactly what we had transferred in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600000,"text":"So, this may sound like genomic alchemy,"},{"time":603000,"text":"but we can, by moving the software of DNA around,"},{"time":607000,"text":"change things quite dramatically."},{"time":611000,"text":"Now I've argued, this is not genesis;"},{"time":613000,"text":"this is building on three and a half billion years of evolution."},{"time":618000,"text":"And I've argued that we're about to perhaps"},{"time":620000,"text":"create a new version of the Cambrian explosion,"},{"time":623000,"text":"where there's massive new speciation"},{"time":627000,"text":"based on this digital design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629000,"text":"Why do this?"},{"time":631000,"text":"I think this is pretty obvious in terms of some of the needs."},{"time":633000,"text":"We're about to go from six and a half"},{"time":635000,"text":"to nine billion people over the next 40 years."},{"time":638000,"text":"To put it in context for myself:"},{"time":640000,"text":"I was born in 1946."},{"time":642000,"text":"There are now three people on the planet"},{"time":644000,"text":"for every one of us that existed in 1946;"},{"time":648000,"text":"within 40 years, there'll be four."},{"time":651000,"text":"We have trouble feeding, providing fresh, clean water,"},{"time":654000,"text":"medicines, fuel"},{"time":656000,"text":"for the six and a half billion."},{"time":659000,"text":"It's going to be a stretch to do it for nine."},{"time":661000,"text":"We use over five billion tons of coal,"},{"time":664000,"text":"30 billion-plus barrels of oil --"},{"time":667000,"text":"that's a hundred million barrels a day."},{"time":671000,"text":"When we try to think of biological processes"},{"time":673000,"text":"or any process to replace that,"},{"time":676000,"text":"it's going to be a huge challenge."},{"time":678000,"text":"Then of course, there's all that"},{"time":680000,"text":"CO2 from this material"},{"time":682000,"text":"that ends up in the atmosphere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"We now, from our discovery around the world,"},{"time":687000,"text":"have a database with about 20 million genes,"},{"time":691000,"text":"and I like to think of these as the design components of the future."},{"time":695000,"text":"The electronics industry only had a dozen or so components,"},{"time":698000,"text":"and look at the diversity that came out of that."},{"time":702000,"text":"We're limited here primarily"},{"time":704000,"text":"by a biological reality"},{"time":706000,"text":"and our imagination."},{"time":709000,"text":"We now have techniques,"},{"time":711000,"text":"because of these rapid methods of synthesis,"},{"time":714000,"text":"to do what we're calling combinatorial genomics."},{"time":718000,"text":"We have the ability now to build a large robot"},{"time":721000,"text":"that can make a million chromosomes a day."},{"time":725000,"text":"When you think of processing these 20 million different genes"},{"time":728000,"text":"or trying to optimize processes"},{"time":730000,"text":"to produce octane or to produce pharmaceuticals,"},{"time":733000,"text":"new vaccines,"},{"time":736000,"text":"we can just with a small team,"},{"time":739000,"text":"do more molecular biology"},{"time":741000,"text":"than the last 20 years of all science."},{"time":744000,"text":"And it's just standard selection:"},{"time":746000,"text":"we can select for viability,"},{"time":748000,"text":"chemical or fuel production,"},{"time":750000,"text":"vaccine production, etc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752000,"text":"This is a screen snapshot"},{"time":755000,"text":"of some true design software"},{"time":758000,"text":"that we're working on to actually be able to sit down"},{"time":761000,"text":"and design species in the computer."},{"time":765000,"text":"You know, we don't know necessarily what it'll look like:"},{"time":768000,"text":"we know exactly what their genetic code looks like."},{"time":771000,"text":"We're focusing on now fourth-generation fuels."},{"time":777000,"text":"You've seen recently, corn to ethanol"},{"time":779000,"text":"is just a bad experiment."},{"time":781000,"text":"We have second- and third-generation fuels"},{"time":783000,"text":"that will be coming out relatively soon"},{"time":786000,"text":"that are sugar, to much higher-value fuels"},{"time":789000,"text":"like octane or different types of butanol."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792000,"text":"But the only way we think that biology"},{"time":795000,"text":"can have a major impact without"},{"time":798000,"text":"further increasing the cost of food and limiting its availability"},{"time":801000,"text":"is if we start with CO2 as its feedstock,"},{"time":804000,"text":"and so we're working with designing cells to go down this road."},{"time":809000,"text":"And we think we'll have the first fourth-generation fuels"},{"time":812000,"text":"in about 18 months."},{"time":814000,"text":"Sunlight and CO2 is one method ..."},{"time":816000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":821000,"text":"but in our discovery around the world,"},{"time":823000,"text":"we have all kinds of other methods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"This is an organism we described in 1996."},{"time":829000,"text":"It lives in the deep ocean,"},{"time":831000,"text":"about a mile and a half deep,"},{"time":833000,"text":"almost at boiling-water temperatures."},{"time":835000,"text":"It takes CO2 to methane"},{"time":838000,"text":"using molecular hydrogen as its energy source."},{"time":841000,"text":"We're looking to see if we can take"},{"time":843000,"text":"captured CO2,"},{"time":845000,"text":"which can easily be piped to sites,"},{"time":847000,"text":"convert that CO2 back into fuel"},{"time":850000,"text":"to drive this process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853000,"text":"So, in a short period of time,"},{"time":855000,"text":"we think that we might be able to increase"},{"time":859000,"text":"what the basic question is of \"What is life?\""},{"time":862000,"text":"We truly, you know,"},{"time":864000,"text":"have modest goals"},{"time":866000,"text":"of replacing the whole petrol-chemical industry --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":869000,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":872000,"text":"Yeah. If you can't do that at TED, where can you? --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":875000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":877000,"text":"become a major source of energy ..."},{"time":879000,"text":"But also, we're now working on using these same tools"},{"time":882000,"text":"to come up with instant sets of vaccines."},{"time":885000,"text":"You've seen this year with flu;"},{"time":887000,"text":"we're always a year behind and a dollar short"},{"time":890000,"text":"when it comes to the right vaccine."},{"time":892000,"text":"I think that can be changed"},{"time":894000,"text":"by building combinatorial vaccines in advance."},{"time":898000,"text":"Here's what the future may begin to look like"},{"time":901000,"text":"with changing, now, the evolutionary tree,"},{"time":905000,"text":"speeding up evolution"},{"time":907000,"text":"with synthetic bacteria, Archaea"},{"time":910000,"text":"and, eventually, eukaryotes."},{"time":914000,"text":"We're a ways away from improving people:"},{"time":916000,"text":"our goal is just to make sure that we have a chance"},{"time":919000,"text":"to survive long enough to maybe do that. Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}